BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:european-ai-society-fund-building-narrative-power-2026@artificialnouvea
 u.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:Deadline: Building Narrative Power: EUR 2m funding and learning pro
 gramme
DESCRIPTION:The European AI & Society Fund is launching Building Narrative 
 Power\, a EUR 2 million funding and learning programme to counter Big Tech
 's dominance over how AI is understood\, and to help people and communitie
 s shape new ways of thinking and talking about the technology they want. T
 he Fund's strategy is to build the power of the public interest community 
 to shape the direction of AI in Europe\; narratives are central to creatin
 g the conditions for a greater say over how AI is adopted and used. THREE 
 THEMES where research shows the public already feels strongly: (1) DATA CE
 NTRES: as the EU aims to triple data centre numbers in the next five to se
 ven years\, pollution\, energy prices and compromised grid access have mob
 ilised communities across the political spectrum\; proposals should explor
 e narrative questions that move communities beyond resistance towards enga
 gement in shaping data centre expansion. (2) AI AND JOBS: 57% of the publi
 c in a recent study expressed concern about how AI will change employment\
 , more pronounced among lower-income people\, and the concern is not only 
 displacement but the quality and nature of work\, autonomy and dignity\; p
 roposals should move the debate from generalised anxiety into a mobilising
  issue that shapes the future of work. (3) YOUNG PEOPLE: beyond the stride
 nt social media ban debate\, young people encounter AI in education\, frie
 ndships and future careers\, and their wider views are rarely heard\; prop
 osals should build narratives that help young people shape the technologie
 s that will influence their lives. LEARNING PROGRAMME: grantees join a com
 munity of practice\, sharing experiences across issues and places\, suppor
 ting each other through delivery and reflecting on which strategies and st
 ories have most salience\, with findings feeding back to the Fund and othe
 r funders. Deadline for first-stage applications is 31 August 2026.\n\nOrg
 anisation: European AI & Society Fund\nLocation: Europe (organisations acr
 oss Europe)\nAward: Grants of up to EUR 150\,000 from a EUR 2 million prog
 ramme\, plus participation in a learning programme and community of practi
 ce. No application fee.\nDuration: Project grant with an accompanying lear
 ning programme\n\nMore: https://europeanaifund.org/newspublications/call-f
 or-proposals-new-e2m-building-narrative-power-funding-and-learning-program
 me/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://europeanaifund.org/newspublications/call-for-proposals-new-e2m-
 building-narrative-power-funding-and-learning-programme/?utm_source=artifi
 cialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Europe (organisations across Europe)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prototype-fund-switzerland-responsible-sustainable-ai-2026-27@artificia
 lnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260907
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260908
SUMMARY:Deadline: Prototype Fund Switzerland 2026-27: Responsible and Susta
 inable AI
DESCRIPTION:Since 2020 the Prototype Fund Switzerland has strengthened the 
 common good with open-source\, public-interest technology\, supporting int
 erdisciplinary teams to develop and test early-stage projects that show ho
 w open source\, data and digital technologies such as AI can create real s
 ocietal value. The 2026-2027 edition focuses on Responsible and Sustainabl
 e AI: building the path toward a more responsible and sustainable AI\, tec
 h and digitalization landscape\, open source and beyond. THIS YEAR'S FOCUS
 : projects that reduce resource use\, energy consumption or emissions\; st
 rengthen accountability\, transparency and governance\; and contribute to 
 resilient and trustworthy digital systems\, including sustainable digitali
 zation and digital sufficiency\, public-interest AI and data infrastructur
 es\, and tools for governance\, oversight or digital sovereignty. PUBLIC I
 NTEREST TECH areas span sustainability and climate\, participation and civ
 ic tech\, education and literacy\, health and inclusion\, and open knowled
 ge and data. WHO THEY FUND: individuals and small teams open to open sourc
 e\, AI and iterative experimentation\, eager to combine technical capabili
 ty with societal and political awareness\, willing to share learnings\, mo
 tivated to work on pressing societal problems through technology\, with an
  early-stage but well-thought-out concept\, and eligible to work in Switze
 rland. SUPPORT: up to CHF 50\,000 in funding\, a 4-month prototyping phase
 \, coaching\, mentoring and workshops\, and access to a strong network acr
 oss tech\, policy and society. Teams are strongly encouraged (though not r
 equired) to publish code\, data or components under open-source licenses a
 nd to document their approach. TIMELINE: applications 21 July to 7 Septemb
 er 2026\; rolling jury selection August-September 2026\; prototyping mid-O
 ctober 2026 to mid-February 2027\; outputs and learnings November 2026 to 
 July 2027. Questions: info@prototypefund.ch.\n\nOrganisation: Prototype Fu
 nd Switzerland (Opendata.ch)\nLocation: Switzerland\; applicants must be e
 ligible to work in Switzerland.\nAward: Up to CHF 50\,000 per project\, pl
 us coaching\, mentoring and workshops and access to a tech/policy/society 
 network. No application fee.\nDuration: 4-month prototyping phase (mid-Oct
 ober 2026 to mid-February 2027)\n\nMore: https://prototypefund.opendata.ch
 /en/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://prototypefund.opendata.ch/en/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrant
 desk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Switzerland\; applicants must be eligible to work in Switzerland.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:talos-ai-policy-leaders-programme-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260614
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260615
SUMMARY:Deadline: Talos Network: AI Policy Leaders Programme 2026 (Autumn c
 ohort)
DESCRIPTION:The Talos Network's Policy Leaders Programme is built for exper
 ienced professionals ready to move into shaping European governance of adv
 anced AI. It runs a part-time virtual European AI Policy Bootcamp (10 Sep 
 - 22 Oct 2026\, weekly Thursday calls\, ~10 hrs/week\, designed around a f
 ull-time job) with a fully-reimbursed week-long policymaking summit in Bru
 ssels (3-9 Oct 2026)\, and a Placement track offering a 12-month paid plac
 ement at a relevant AI-focused organisation (base EUR 5\,000/month for Bru
 ssels). Fellows get intensive 1-1 mentoring and career coaching\, access t
 o the Talos Network and alumni\, a curated senior peer cohort\, and tailor
 ed financial support. ELIGIBILITY: experienced professionals (around 8-10+
  years) in high-stakes environments such as government\, international org
 anisations\, think tanks\, industry or academia\, with a track record of i
 nfluencing senior decision-makers\, looking to transition into AI governan
 ce or strengthen the AI dimension of their existing work\; Europe-focused.
  Application deadline 14 June 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Talos Network\nLocati
 on: Europe (virtual bootcamp + week-long Brussels summit\; placements in B
 russels or other European cities)\nAward: Placement track: a 12-month paid
  placement at an AI-focused organisation\, base EUR 5\,000/month for Bruss
 els (adjusted for cost of living elsewhere). Plus a fully-reimbursed 6-day
  Brussels policymaking summit\, tailored financial support (coworking\, co
 nference attendance\, career-transition funding)\, and intensive 1-1 mento
 ring. No application fee.\nDuration: Virtual bootcamp 10 Sep - 22 Oct 2026
  (approx. 10 hrs/week) plus a 12-month paid placement (placement track)\n\
 nMore: https://www.talosnetwork.org/policy-leaders-programme?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.talosnetwork.org/policy-leaders-programme?utm_source=artifi
 cialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Europe (virtual bootcamp + week-long Brussels summit\; placements 
 in Brussels or other European cities)
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
